<section class="detail" id="sparse_size/1">


  <div class="detail-header">
    <a href="#sparse_size/1" class="detail-link" data-no-tooltip="" aria-label="Link to this function">
      <i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i>
    </a>
    <div class="heading-with-actions">

      <div class="signature-row">


            <h1 class="signature" translate="no">sparse_size(Array :: <a href="#t:array/0">array</a>())<span class="signature-arrow">&nbsp;-&gt;&nbsp;</span><span class="signature-result"><a href="../../../../lib/../erts/doc/html/erlang.html#t:non_neg_integer/0">non_neg_integer</a>()</span></h1>




          <a href="https://github.com/erlang/otp/blob/master/lib/stdlib/src/array.erl#L1858" class="icon-action" rel="help nofollow" aria-label="View Source">
            <i class="ri-code-s-slash-line" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="docstring">



<p>Gets the number of entries in the array up until the last non-default-valued
entry.</p><p>That is, returns <code class="inline">I+1</code> if <code class="inline">I</code> is the last non-default-valued entry in
the array, or zero if no such entry exists.</p><h2 id="sparse_size/1-examples" class="section-heading"><a href="#sparse_size/1-examples" class="hover-link"><i class="ri-link-m" aria-hidden="true"></i></a><span class="text">Examples</span></h2><pre><code class="makeup erlang" translate="no"><span class="gp unselectable">1&gt; </span><span class="n">A</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="o">=</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">array</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">set</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-1">(</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="mi">42</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nc">array</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">new</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-2">(</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-2">)</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-1">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">2&gt; </span><span class="nc">array</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">size</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-3">(</span><span class="n">A</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-3">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="gp unselectable">3&gt; </span><span class="nc">array</span><span class="p">:</span><span class="nf">sparse_size</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-4">(</span><span class="n">A</span><span class="p" data-group-id="0526559189-4">)</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="mi">4</span></code></pre><p>See also <a href="#resize/1"><code class="inline">resize/1</code></a>, <a href="#size/1"><code class="inline">size/1</code></a>.</p>
  </section>
</section>
